sdata (0.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Phase 3 complete: SELECT row filter, BY-group processing, filter-aware
    LAG/NEXT/RECNO/BOF/EOF, SELECT /ALL and bare BY to cancel filter/grouping.
  * Add manpage (sdata.1).
  * Expand HELP text for aggregate and statistical functions.
  * Add explanatory comments throughout interpreter, evaluator, and parser.

 -- John L. Ries <john@theyarnbard.com>  Mon, 06 Apr 2026 22:00:00 -0700

sdata (0.2.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Implement AND, OR, and XOR boolean operators.
  * Fix END SELECT parsing and blank line handling inside SELECT blocks.
  * Fix SELECT block parsing and multi-line support in REPL.
  * Route error/warning messages to both output file and stderr.
  * Allow variable and expression bounds in DIM command.
  * Fix case-sensitivity bug in OBS and LAG functions.
  * Expand arrays in ARRAY command constituent list.
  * Fix SORT to save output dataset and print completion message.
  * Replace heapsort with stable merge sort.
  * SlackBuild: use gnatmake instead of gprbuild.
  * Remove unused sciada dependency from all build systems.
  * Add README.md.

 -- John L. Ries <john@theyarnbard.com>  Wed, 02 Apr 2026 12:00:00 -0700

sdata (0.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Performance optimizations for SORT and data steps.
  * Replaced bubble sort with heapsort (O(n log n)).
  * Optimized Value type using Unbounded_String to reduce memory footprint.
  * Optimized table access using Ada 2012 Reference types.
  * Fixed FPATH not executing in REPL.
  * Fixed several CSV parsing and header preservation bugs.

 -- John L. Ries <john@theyarnbard.com>  Mon, 30 Mar 2026 11:00:00 -0700

